@LBA2_PRODUCT_NAME@ @LBA2_VERSION_STRING@
====================================================

@LBA2_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION@

This is a portable Windows build. No installer, no registry entries.
Unzip anywhere and run.


GAME DATA
---------

This fork doesn't include the game data — you need a legitimate copy
of Little Big Adventure 2 / Twinsen's Odyssey from GOG, Steam, or
your original retail CD.

The simplest setup: drop lba2.hqr (and the rest of the retail data
files: music, video, vox, etc.) directly next to @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe.

The engine also looks for a "data" or "game" subfolder next to the
.exe, so this layout works too:

    @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe
    data\
        lba2.hqr
        music\
        video\
        ...

Alternative ways to point at game data:

    @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe --game-dir "C:\path\to\game"

    set LBA2_GAME_DIR=C:\path\to\game
    @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe


RUNNING
-------

Double-click @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe, or run from cmd.exe / PowerShell.

If the game can't find its data, it'll print the directories it tried
to a log file in your user profile.


